46:26.169 --> 46:27.231
There are no clues.

46:29.134 --> 46:31.377
The greatest psychiatrist on earth couldn't read it.

46:32.459 --> 46:36.746
So in despair, I look at his tiny little face staring off my mind and the strangest thing happened.

46:37.127 --> 46:41.874
See, I'm his dad and I found I could read his face pretty easy.

46:42.370 --> 46:46.194
that the weird little things that go on in his head, kind of how he's feeling.

46:46.474 --> 46:48.216
I mean, don't be too impressed.

46:48.236 --> 46:51.379
I could work out what he had for lunch because it was still on his t-shirt.

46:53.641 --> 46:58.205
And so as I looked at him, I thought, I think I might know what he's trying to say.

46:58.225 --> 47:04.992
So then I looked back at the scribbles and I cleared my throat and began to read.

47:06.253 --> 47:08.275
And as I did so, this little head is nodding.

47:09.316 --> 47:11.698
And at the end, he says, well done, Daddy.

47:12.098 --> 47:12.679
Good reading.

47:14.541 --> 47:17.704
And I said, thank you very much, because it was actually some of the greatest reading I'd ever done.

47:20.187 --> 47:20.868
Here's the thing.

47:21.628 --> 47:29.057
You think your prayer life is about having all the right words for God, but they're just scribbles.

47:29.217 --> 47:31.980
They're just sounds that you emit into the ether.

47:33.361 --> 47:37.586
He's your father in heaven, and he knows you better than anyone else.

47:37.890 --> 47:42.796
And he understands the funny little things going on in your head and how you're feeling and what you had for lunch.

47:43.817 --> 47:54.249
